  "2026-06-28T20:23:16.739Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: implemented MCP action-schema parity for guide.list, health.brief, validate.parentCycleSeverity, and contracts.full; added parentCycleSeverity parameter metadata; broadened list metadata for guide; regenerated full contracts snapshot; added SDK parity regression tests. Also fixed scripts/run-tests.mjs so repo test runs clear ambient PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT, preventing installed-CLI linked-test launches from forcing package runtimes to load dist SDK during source tests. Verification: pm test pm-zx13 --run --progress --pm-context tracker --override-linked-pm-context passed all 8 linked checks, including env -u PM_PATH -u PM_GLOBAL_PATH node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage with 100/100/100/100 coverage, sentry/telemetry gate, focused parity test, build, contracts:check, lint, security:scan, and typecheck."
  "2026-06-28T20:24:52.041Z",codex-agent,"Final local gates before PR: pnpm changelog:pm:check used pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and reported CHANGELOG.md unchanged (item_count 1363); git diff --check passed; static-quality-gate --json passed with source docstrings 244/244 and exported docstrings 1858/1858; fresh isolated temp smoke passed under sandboxed PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH for init/create/health --brief/validate --parent-cycle-severity/contracts schemas for health.brief, contracts.full, and validate.parentCycleSeverity. pm health --check-only --summary was ok with pre-existing telemetry_queue_pending warning; pm validate history drift ok with pre-existing resolution metadata warnings."
  "2026-06-28T20:33:44.467Z",codex-agent,"Review feedback: Gemini and Greptile both flagged that health.brief fell back to the placeholder schema description 'Brief.' because PM_TOOL_PARAMETER_METADATA had no brief entry. I reproduced the generated placeholder in full.json and will add explicit brief metadata, regenerate contracts, and rerun the focused contract checks. Greptile also suggested a fully generic parity loop; current command flag contracts include many intentional non-MCP/global/legacy alias gaps, so I am keeping the regression test targeted for this PR rather than adding a broad false-positive guard."
  "2026-06-28T20:35:29.251Z",codex-agent,"Review response implemented: added PM_TOOL_PARAMETER_METADATA.brief with low-token description/examples, regenerated contracts after rebuilding dist so health/list-family schemas no longer expose the placeholder 'Brief.', and added parity test coverage for the health brief description/examples. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/action-schema-parity.spec.ts (3 tests), pm test pm-zx13 --run --match action-schema-parity --progress --pm-context tracker --override-linked-pm-context, pnpm build, pnpm contracts:check, pnpm typecheck, and git diff --check."
